Aboitiz, PAL, PLDT, SM Investments: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   S h i y i n   C h e n
-- 
2011-10-17T00:26:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-17/aboitiz-pal-pldt-sm-investments-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index increased 0.5 percent
to 4,153.40.  Aboitiz Power Corp. (AP)  : The  Philippines ’ Aboitiz Power
and  Manila Electric Co. (MER)   are in talks with creditors to
help fund the construction of a 600 megawatt power plant,
Aboitiz Power President Erramon Aboitiz said. Aboitiz Power
gained 0.7 percent to 29.70 pesos. Manila Electric climbed 2
percent to 246 pesos.  PAL Holdings Inc. (PAL)  : Philippine Airlines, the
company’s unit, isn’t for sale, President Jaime Bautista told
ABS-CBN News. Still, Bautista said the carrier will need equity
from investors to grow, according to the report. The shares
advanced 1.6 percent to 7.01 pesos.  Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co. (TEL)  : the
nation’s largest phone company has agreed to sell some if its
so-called 3G frequencies, paving the way for regulatory approval
of its purchase of Digital Telecommunications Philippines Inc.
(DGTL PM), the Manila Times reported, citing people it didn’t
identify. PLDT added 0.2 percent to 2,204 pesos. Digitel
retreated 1.3 percent to 1.50 pesos.  SM Investments Corp. (SM)  : Third-quarter profit at the
holding company of Philippine billionaire  Henry Sy  may have
increased 13 percent to 14 percent from a year ago, Chief
Financial Officer Jose Sio said. The company may also invest in
power and tourism projects, he said. The stock advanced 1.4
percent to 530 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shiyin Chen in Singapore at 
 schen37@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
